<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<subsection xml:id="make-up_policy" component="exams">
  <title>Make-up Policy</title>
  
  <p>
   Students who cannot complete an exam due to a University-related activity or an <alert>excused</alert> absence 
   must contact me <alert>before</alert> the exam in the case of a University activity or within 72 hours in the 
   case of an emergency. If a make-up exam is granted, the comprehensive final exam will replace the missed exam grade
   in addition to counting as the final exam grade. If a make-up exam is not granted, the missed exam will be recorded as a zero.
  </p>
  <!-- <p>
    In the event of one missed exam due to absence, the Final Exam can be used to replace the missing exam.
    Further missed exams will result in a grade of zero.
    If a University sponsored activity requires you to miss an exam, you must complete the exam in advance.
  </p>
-->

